Conflicts: alsalib-dev
Description: Advanced Linux Sound Architecture (development)
 ALSA is an effort to create a modular sound system for Linux,
 while maintaining full compatibility with OSS/Lite.
 .
 These are the files necessary for development.

Package: libasound2-plugins
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: libasound2 (= ${Source-Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Advanced Linux Sound Architecture (additional plugins)
 ALSA is an effort to create a modular sound system for Linux,
 while maintaining full compatibility with OSS/Lite.
 .
 These are additional plugins for libasound2, not included in the main
 package. Currently, the JACK plugin is included.

Package: libasound2-doc
Architecture: all
Section: libdevel
Description: Advanced Linux Sound Architecture (developer's documentation)
 ALSA is an effort to create a modular sound system for Linux,
 while maintaining full compatibility with OSS/Lite.
 .
 These are the documentation files for the development package,
 libasound2-dev.
